# Placeholder so the `companions/` directory always exists in the repo.
#
# CI stages companion repo checkouts (openagentic, sdk, oat)
# into this directory before building the openagentic-ui image — see
# .github/workflows/cd-build-push.yml job "Stage companions for UI docs".
#
# The openagentic-ui Dockerfile's docs-generator stage does:
#   COPY companions /companions
#   ENV DOCS_COMPANION_ROOT=/companions
#
# ...so scripts/generate-docs.ts can resolve companion project paths via
# utils.ts companionPath() → /companions/<project> instead of the
# developer-box sibling layout.
#
# On a local docker build without CI staging, this directory stays empty
# and each companion generator gracefully skips (findFiles returns []).
